Data Scientist		SmartAsset		New York City, NY, US		<div class="rich-text" itemprop="description"><strong>Listing Info<br /><br /></strong>SmartAsset is quickly becoming the web’s default destination for personal finance advice.  Our software integrates over 130 different data sources to provide automated answers to important personal finance questions.  Between our natural dependency on data and an incredible growth rate we generate an enormous amount of (currently under-utilized) user, product engagement and marketing data.  We are looking for an outstanding Data Scientist to rationalize, analyze and manage our rapidly growing data-resources across product, monetization and digital marketing.<br /><br /><strong>Responsibilities<br /></strong><ul><li>Work closely with the Product, Marketing and Tech teams to develop, implement and interpret experiments designed to improve user satisfaction, marketing or monetization metrics</li> <li>Develop a centralized dashboard for all SmartAsset data</li> <li>King of the Key Performance Indicator:  you will identify, measure and optimize the metrics most closely with our business goals</li> <li>Use statistical software packages of your choice to analyze SmartAsset data</li> <li>Use analytical ability to support product development in areas requiring particularly challenging math or data work</li> <br /></ul><strong>Example Projects<br /></strong><ul><li>Analyze data from search marketing campaigns and identify underperformers, overachievers and opportunities for improvement</li> <li>Analyze consumer satisfaction metrics:  which user cohorts are positively / negatively disposed, how can we use that data to improve our user experience</li> <li>How are different financial product prices changing over time:  what functionality can we provide users to better alert them to the probability of future price changes</li> <br /><br /></ul><strong>Requirements<br /></strong><ul><li>Self-motivated and naturally curious about causal relationships between variables</li> <li>Deep understanding of probability and statistics</li> <li>Professional experience using statistical analysis to drive actionable outcomes</li> <li>Bachelors plus 5 years experience working with statistics and / or data analysis</li> <br /></ul><strong>Some nice perks of the job<br /></strong><ul><li>Work to solve problems that bring real positive impact to people's lives</li> <li>Help shape the future of the consumer finance industry</li> <li>Fun work environment with passionate colleagues</li> <li>Meritocracy! We reward the awesome</li> <br /></ul><strong>Details<br /></strong><ul><li>This is a full-time position, based in our New York City office</li> <li>Compensation: competitive salary with full medical and dental coverage</li> <br /><br /></ul><strong>About SmartAsset (We're Kind Of a Big Deal)<br /><br /></strong>SmartAsset is a venture backed, Y Combinator Company. We use our patent pending financial modeling technology to provide accurate, interactive answers to important personal finance questions. We are a consumer advocate, recommending specific strategies so people can make smarter decisions and save money. We have been covered by over 50 publications, including the New York Times, Techcrunch, Fast Company and the US News and World Report.<br /><br /></div><div class="rich-text" itemprop="description">SmartAsset is a financial technology company that uses data to provide free, actionable advice for big financial decisions on issues including home buying, retirement, life insurance, student loans, refinance, credit cards and checking accounts. At the heart of our service is a decision engine and optimization tool that measures the efficacy of different strategies, quantifies the true cost of financing alternatives and recommends specific financial products based on their suitability and cost to your specific situation.</div>